S & P says cuts Ashikaga Bank ' s long - term ratings . Standard & Poor ' s Corp said on Monday that it had lowered its long - term counterparty and certificates of deposit ( CD ) ratings of Ashikaga Bank Ltd to BBB - from BBB . S & P said in a statement that it had affirmed Ashikaga ' s short - term counterparty and CD ratings at A3 . The outlook for the ratings remained negative , S & P said . Ashikaga ' s loan losses could grow as collateral values remain under stress , S & P said . It added that the bank ' s financial parameters would be pressured until its asset - quality problems become more controllable . Ashikaga ' s response to the challenges posed by financial deregulation would likely be delayed if its asset - quality problems take more time to resolve than those of its peers , S & P said . 
